788
00:56:27,417 --> 00:56:30,220
I should have tailed Ms. Jang instead.

789
00:56:32,989 --> 00:56:34,958
-Yu-chang.
-Yes.

790
00:56:35,358 --> 00:56:38,928
How do I set this photo as my wallpaper?

791
00:56:39,062 --> 00:56:41,297
Oh. Hold on a moment.

792
00:56:44,567 --> 00:56:46,903
Are you really going to use this?

793
00:56:47,070 --> 00:56:48,037
Yes.

794
00:56:48,104 --> 00:56:51,141
You have a very strong stomach.

795
00:56:54,110 --> 00:56:55,845
Hey, it's you.

796
00:56:56,446 --> 00:56:58,448
Isn't Ms. Jang in?

797
00:56:58,615 --> 00:57:00,984
She went to court for a trial at 2 p.m.

798
00:57:01,317 --> 00:57:02,752
She went with Mr. Cha.

799
00:57:03,319 --> 00:57:04,654
Really?

800
00:57:05,121 --> 00:57:06,322
Thank you.

801
00:57:07,157 --> 00:57:08,091
Do it.

802
00:57:08,158 --> 00:57:10,093
Are you sure?

803
00:57:10,226 --> 00:57:12,195
Just do as you're told.

804
00:57:18,768 --> 00:57:20,870
-Yes?
-Is the trial over?

805
00:57:21,371 --> 00:57:23,306
No, we didn't even get to start.

806
00:57:23,506 --> 00:57:25,542
-Why?
-The lawyer didn't come.

807
00:57:25,975 --> 00:57:29,913
She didn't come for 30 minutes,
so we had the trial postponed.

808
00:57:31,314 --> 00:57:32,715
Why didn't she come?

809
00:57:32,782 --> 00:57:34,050
Who knows?

810
00:57:34,217 --> 00:57:36,719
The judge kept calling,
but couldn't get hold of her.

811
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:45,929
Park Su-ha!

812
00:57:50,033 --> 00:57:52,135
Do you know where Ms. Jjang is?

813
00:57:52,202 --> 00:57:53,236
Ms. Jjang?

814
00:57:53,570 --> 00:57:54,838
Isn't she in trial?

815
00:57:55,104 --> 00:57:56,873
It must have started at 2:00 p.m.

816
00:57:57,240 --> 00:57:59,108
She wasn't there. They couldn't reach her.

817
00:57:59,342 --> 00:58:01,578
That can't be. Did you try calling?

818
00:58:01,744 --> 00:58:04,881
No, I lost my phone to a thief.

819
00:58:06,749 --> 00:58:08,585
Hello? Ms. Jjang?

820
00:58:11,621 --> 00:58:12,922
It got cut off.

821
00:58:13,857 --> 00:58:15,825
I walked her to court.

822
00:58:19,562 --> 00:58:21,764
Is it because of that article?

823
00:58:22,398 --> 00:58:24,701
No, that can't be.

824
00:58:26,870 --> 00:58:28,104
By chance,

825
00:58:28,471 --> 00:58:30,974
did you tell Ms. Jjang about my father?

826
00:58:31,774 --> 00:58:32,609
What?

827
00:58:34,310 --> 00:58:35,445
Yes.

828
00:58:36,346 --> 00:58:38,381
While going through my desk,

829
00:58:38,648 --> 00:58:41,217
she found the articles
Min Jun-guk had sent.

830
00:58:44,220 --> 00:58:46,456
I'm sorry. I had no choice.

831
00:58:46,856 --> 00:58:49,626
Does she know everything?

832
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:51,427
Yes.

833
00:58:51,961 --> 00:58:53,096
Almost.

834
00:58:56,199 --> 00:58:57,200
So...

835
00:58:58,101 --> 00:58:59,602
That's why she disappeared.

836
00:58:59,669 --> 00:59:02,205
No. This has nothing to do
with her finding out.

837
00:59:02,272 --> 00:59:04,207
-This is--
-What do you know?

838
00:59:06,609 --> 00:59:08,144
Why did you tell her?

839
00:59:14,350 --> 00:59:15,418
Park Su-ha!

840
00:59:15,485 --> 00:59:16,619
Park Su-ha!

841
00:59:20,323 --> 00:59:21,424
Sir.

842
00:59:21,591 --> 00:59:23,927
Let's change the person
we are in charge of now.

843
00:59:24,027 --> 00:59:27,564
I'll take Ms. Jang.
You should take Park Su-ha.

844
00:59:27,864 --> 00:59:31,301
No, we should stick to
who we're in charge of.

845
00:59:31,768 --> 00:59:34,837
I think I'm going to die
from following him.

846
00:59:35,171 --> 00:59:36,606
Hurry up.

847
00:59:36,839 --> 00:59:37,974
You're going to lose him.

848
00:59:39,142 --> 00:59:41,210
He's really fast.

849
00:59:43,880 --> 00:59:45,448
Isn't that?

850
00:59:47,283 --> 00:59:48,418
Did you see Ms. Jjang?

851
00:59:48,484 --> 00:59:51,487
-You went in with her.
-So you didn't see her come out?

852
00:59:51,621 --> 00:59:52,922
No. Why?

853
00:59:53,122 --> 00:59:54,190
She's disappeared.

854
00:59:55,358 --> 00:59:57,727
-She didn't come to court.
-That can't be.

855
00:59:59,762 --> 01:00:02,098
I stayed right here.
I didn't even go to the toilet.

856
01:00:02,465 --> 01:00:05,802
Unless she snuck out on purpose,
I couldn't have missed her.

857
01:00:05,902 --> 01:00:08,304
She's not answering her phone.
Where did she go?

858
01:00:45,642 --> 01:00:50,580
I'm not the one who started all of this!

859
01:00:50,780 --> 01:00:53,149
It was your father!

860
01:00:56,719 --> 01:00:58,921
Is there anything
else you haven't told me?

861
01:00:59,889 --> 01:01:01,557
Is that all you lied about?

862
01:01:22,211 --> 01:01:23,780
What should I tell her?

863
01:01:24,714 --> 01:01:26,616
No excuses will work.

864
01:01:27,884 --> 01:01:29,819
What if she hangs up
when she hears my voice?

865
01:01:30,953 --> 01:01:34,924
Will I be able to live
if this is the end for us?

866
01:01:52,642 --> 01:01:53,676
Hello?

867
01:01:53,743 --> 01:01:56,012
It's Su-ha. Don't hang up on me.

868
01:01:56,512 --> 01:01:59,015
I heard everything from Mr. Cha.
You heard about my father--

869
01:01:59,082 --> 01:02:02,518
I've been waiting for you to call,
Park Su-ha.

870
01:02:05,354 --> 01:02:07,056
Are you looking for Jang Hye-seong?

871
01:02:22,905 --> 01:02:25,908
On July 26, 2013, at 3:10 p.m.,

872
01:02:26,442 --> 01:02:28,411
she was kidnapped by Min Jun-guk.

873
01:02:29,278 --> 01:02:31,347
Two hours and thirty minutes later,

874
01:02:31,981 --> 01:02:35,218
our 11-year story came to an end.

875
01:02:37,620 --> 01:02:39,689
